Newhaven Secondary School celebrates an 87% pass rate in the 2015 matric examinations, with two of their learners achieving a remarkable 8 A s. The school&#8217;s Deputy Principal, D Naidoo, stated that the outstanding results are due to a great deal of discipline from the 2015 learners and sheer hard work that educators had also put in throughout the year.One of the top achieving learners, Lisha Ramcharan, said that she plans to study Commerce at the University of KwaZulu-Natal. Her advice to future matriculants is to concentrate in class, persevere and find a healthy balance between work and play.